# NethWorksNet – Personal Website

## What It Is

A single-page personal portfolio/blog site. Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS, no framework or build step. Uses ES modules and CDN scripts.

## Key Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.html` | Shell: header, nav, main content area |
| `javascript/app.js` | SPA logic: tab switching, content injection, nav animation |
| `javascript/blog.js` | Blog module: loads posts from `posts.json`, fetches Markdown |
| `css/styles.css` | All styles |
| `blog/*.md` | Markdown posts |
| `blog/posts.json` | Post metadata (run `node scripts/update_posts.js` to regenerate) |
| `scripts/update_posts.js` | Node script: scans `blog/*.md`, updates `posts.json` |

## Tabs / Content Map

- **whois** (`data-tab="about"`): GitHub card (nethrose) + Google Drive PDF embed
- **blog**: List of posts from `blog/`, click to render Markdown

## Dependencies

- **marked** (CDN): Markdown → HTML
- **gray-matter** (Node): Frontmatter parsing in `update_posts.js`
- Requires a local server (e.g. `npx serve`) to serve `/blog/` for fetch

